WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:03.830
Previously on "Kevin
(Probably) Saves the World"...

00:03.830 --> 00:05.120
-I'm a messenger from God.
-Oh, good.

00:05.120 --> 00:06.750
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:06.750 --> 00:08.250
The only job
you have in life

00:08.250 --> 00:09.580
is to build up
your spiritual powers

00:09.580 --> 00:12.290
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

00:12.290 --> 00:15.080
God is gonna show you how
to find the other righteous.

00:15.080 --> 00:17.420
And there was
a mariachi band?

00:17.420 --> 00:19.580
I know where we'll find
the first righteous!

00:19.580 --> 00:20.750
Laos?

00:20.750 --> 00:22.420
Laos.

00:22.420 --> 00:24.460
When are you gonna
ask Amy out?

00:24.460 --> 00:26.380
-What do you think?
-No.

00:26.380 --> 00:27.920
If you were to ask me out,
I would say "Yes."

00:27.920 --> 00:30.620
Hi. I'm a good friend
of Kevin's. My name is Dave.

00:30.620 --> 00:32.830
Since when can you
reveal yourself?

00:32.830 --> 00:34.330
Since...forever.

00:34.330 --> 00:37.790
Dave's the one who told the rest
of us not to listen to you.

00:37.790 --> 00:39.750
She's saying you'll find a whole
new generation of the righteous.

00:39.750 --> 00:42.500
I think there aren't anymore.
So which one of us is right?

00:42.500 --> 00:44.290
I don't know.

00:44.290 --> 00:52.500
♪♪

00:52.500 --> 00:55.120
Kevin:
I can't believe we're here!

00:55.120 --> 00:57.420
Didn't think there'd
be so many people.

00:57.420 --> 00:58.920
You're alright. You know
who you're looking for.

00:58.920 --> 01:00.250
[ Gasps ]

01:00.250 --> 01:02.000
Red coat, red hat --
there.

01:03.830 --> 01:05.830
Wait. Where'd he go?

01:05.830 --> 01:11.580
♪♪

01:11.580 --> 01:13.000
Kevin?

01:15.830 --> 01:17.040
Kevin!

01:17.040 --> 01:18.620
I found him. This way.
Ohh.

01:18.620 --> 01:20.580
That's him.

01:20.580 --> 01:21.710
[ Chuckles ]

01:21.710 --> 01:24.540
This is it. I can't --
I can't believe it.

01:24.540 --> 01:26.460
I can.

01:26.460 --> 01:33.380
♪♪

01:37.040 --> 01:38.750
I-I don't understand.

01:39.670 --> 01:41.960
Look over there.

01:41.960 --> 01:47.920
♪♪

01:47.920 --> 01:49.790
No.

01:49.790 --> 01:52.580
It didn't work.

01:52.580 --> 01:53.880
You were wrong.

01:53.880 --> 01:56.290
You did this, Yvette.

01:56.290 --> 01:58.080
This is all your fault.

01:59.880 --> 02:02.000
Kevin! No! Ohh!

02:02.000 --> 02:03.540
[ Gasps ]

02:03.540 --> 02:05.040
♪ Dashing through the snow ♪

02:05.040 --> 02:08.040
♪ In a one-horse open sleigh ♪

02:08.040 --> 02:09.540
♪ O'er the fields we go ♪

02:09.540 --> 02:12.210
Hey!
When did you get here?

02:12.210 --> 02:16.540
Um, a-about 7:30,
I guess.

02:16.540 --> 02:18.790
Oh, I mean --
Uh, uh, yeah.

02:18.790 --> 02:21.790
That's great.
To -- To see ya.

02:21.790 --> 02:24.790
Well, maybe it was
closer to 8:00.

02:24.790 --> 02:27.580
Oh. Sure. Okay.

02:27.580 --> 02:30.040
♪ Jingle all the way ♪

02:30.040 --> 02:31.170
-Good morning.
-Hey.

02:31.170 --> 02:33.670
I found a flight to Laos
for $2,000.

02:33.670 --> 02:35.580
Oh, good, good. Good.

02:35.580 --> 02:38.500
No, not good.
Do you have $2,000?

02:38.500 --> 02:42.620
Hold on. Hold on!
7:45! That's it!

02:42.620 --> 02:45.040
Oh.
That's the exact time
of my arrival!

02:45.040 --> 02:50.830
We're still talking.
Cool.

02:50.830 --> 02:54.540
♪♪

02:54.540 --> 02:56.830
Ah! Laos!

02:56.830 --> 02:59.920
[ Speaking Lao ]

02:59.920 --> 03:01.420
Wait.
What is happening?

03:01.420 --> 03:03.250
Remember Tammy?
Her parents were from Laos.

03:03.250 --> 03:05.330
They didn't speak
a word of English.

03:05.330 --> 03:06.670
They loved me.

03:06.670 --> 03:08.880
Wow! That -- Wow.

03:08.880 --> 03:10.250
You sp-- Okay.

03:10.250 --> 03:12.170
Are you planning
a trip?

03:12.170 --> 03:14.080
Oh. Yeah.
I'm trying to.

03:14.080 --> 03:17.330
All I know is that I have to
go to the, um, Nyindi Hotel,

03:17.330 --> 03:22.920
which I found out is in,
uh, Luang...Prabang?

03:22.920 --> 03:25.540
[ Chuckles ] I've always
dreamed of going to Laos.

03:25.540 --> 03:27.830
The furthest I've been
outside Texas is Austin,

03:27.830 --> 03:30.540
which...is in Texas.

03:30.540 --> 03:32.500
Yeah, well,
I don't even know

03:32.500 --> 03:34.380
how I'll afford the
plane ticket, which, uh --

03:34.380 --> 03:36.790
Oh, actually, I still
owe you for breakfast.

03:36.790 --> 03:39.290
Oh. No. I was just coming over
to tell you, you're all set.

03:39.290 --> 03:41.210
That dude paid your bill.

03:41.210 --> 03:43.830
Hey, Sam!
You didn't need to do that!

03:43.830 --> 03:45.080
No, no. No arguments.

03:45.080 --> 03:46.960
You gave me
a new lease on life.

03:46.960 --> 03:48.960
I gave you
a breakfast burrito.

03:48.960 --> 03:50.540
-So now we're even.
-Totally.

03:50.540 --> 03:52.380
-[ Laughs ]
-Hey, uh, where you going?

03:52.380 --> 03:53.830
Mmm.

03:53.830 --> 03:56.710
Uh, Laos, if I can
afford the plane ticket.

03:56.710 --> 03:58.080
Well... [Scoffs]
Let's get you a ticket.

03:58.080 --> 04:00.210
-When do you want to go?
-Oh, no! You don't need to --

04:00.210 --> 04:01.830
No! Listen,
when I was a salesman,

04:01.830 --> 04:03.420
I traveled all the time.

04:03.420 --> 04:06.380
I racked up a butt-ton
of airline miles.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.960
That's a lot of miles.

04:07.960 --> 04:10.170
You should use the miles
before they expire.

04:11.620 --> 04:13.540
-Really?
-Yes!

04:13.540 --> 04:14.750
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

04:16.290 --> 04:20.580
Uh, you wouldn't have enough
miles for two, would you?

04:20.580 --> 04:26.380
♪♪

04:26.380 --> 04:32.420
♪♪

04:32.420 --> 04:34.620
♪ Just hear those
sleigh bells jingling ♪

04:34.620 --> 04:36.500
♪ Ring-ting, a-tingling, too ♪

04:36.500 --> 04:38.210
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:38.210 --> 04:39.620
♪ Come on, it's lovely weather ♪

04:39.620 --> 04:41.620
♪ For a sleigh ride
together with you ♪

04:41.620 --> 04:43.080
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:43.080 --> 04:44.500
-Perfect spot.
-Here?

04:44.500 --> 04:45.500
Yes!

04:45.500 --> 04:47.000
Yep.

04:47.000 --> 04:48.330
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:48.330 --> 04:50.000
-Up you go!
-Alright. Here we go.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.620
♪ It's lovely weather for a
sleigh ride together with you ♪

04:51.620 --> 04:53.040
We're gonna need to get
a little bit over there.

04:53.040 --> 04:54.460
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:54.460 --> 04:56.670
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:56.670 --> 04:59.580
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

04:59.580 --> 05:02.620
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

05:02.620 --> 05:06.380
♪♪

05:06.380 --> 05:10.580
♪ Our cheeks are nice and rosy,
and comfy and cozy are we ♪

05:10.580 --> 05:11.750
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

05:11.750 --> 05:13.500
♪ We're snuggled up together ♪

05:13.500 --> 05:15.710
♪ Like two birds of a feather
would be ♪

05:15.710 --> 05:17.080
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

05:17.080 --> 05:20.460
♪ Let's take this road before us
and sing a chorus or two ♪

05:20.460 --> 05:23.170
Okay. Alright.
One, two, three, go!

05:23.170 --> 05:26.250
♪ It's lovely weather for a
sleigh ride together with you ♪

05:26.250 --> 05:27.790
♪ Ring-a-ling, a-ling,
Ding, dong, ding ♪

05:27.790 --> 05:29.580
Oh, my God!

05:29.580 --> 05:30.920
Ahh.

05:30.920 --> 05:34.040
You are just like Mom.

05:34.040 --> 05:35.460
Nobody loved Christmas
like her.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.080
No.

05:37.080 --> 05:38.460
I stopped
at 10,000 lights.

05:38.460 --> 05:40.080
I thought that was
a good threshold between

05:40.080 --> 05:42.420
classy and insane.

05:42.420 --> 05:46.000
I mean, is it, though?
[ Chuckles ]

05:46.000 --> 05:48.210
We didn't really do Christmas
last year.

05:48.210 --> 05:51.080
It was too close
to losing Jon.

05:51.080 --> 05:53.540
I don't know. It just
felt like the right time.

05:53.540 --> 05:54.710
I was ready.

05:54.710 --> 05:56.960
Well, it looks awesome.

05:56.960 --> 05:58.080
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.

05:58.080 --> 05:59.500
There's still
more decorating to do.

05:59.500 --> 06:01.460
We're gonna put up the
Christmas tree tonight.

06:01.460 --> 06:05.000
Oh! Yeah, I wanted
to talk to you about --

06:05.000 --> 06:06.250
Uh, well.
[ Clears throat ]

06:06.250 --> 06:10.000
I have to go out of town,
um, tonight.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.540
A little -- little trip
with Tyler, actually.

06:13.540 --> 06:16.040
Oh. Okay. Where?

06:16.040 --> 06:19.460
Uh, it's --
Uh, it's...Laos.

06:19.460 --> 06:23.210
To -- To Laos,
the country of -- of Laos.

06:23.210 --> 06:25.040
Well, Tammy's family
always did like Tyler

06:25.040 --> 06:26.620
more than
they like her, so...

06:26.620 --> 06:28.290
[ Gasps ]

06:28.290 --> 06:31.290
Yeah. Exactly. That's why --
That's why we're going.

06:32.620 --> 06:34.580
You better be back
by Christmas.

06:34.580 --> 06:35.750
Oh, y-- I promise.

06:35.750 --> 06:38.670
With Laos presents.

06:38.670 --> 06:41.920
Laotian. Lotion?
How do you say that?

06:41.920 --> 06:43.620
Forget it. I'll tell you
when I get back.

06:45.540 --> 06:47.750
Ooh-ooh!

06:47.750 --> 06:49.000
Very unfortunate.

06:53.620 --> 06:57.500
I was going for serial-killer
mugshot, so success.

06:57.500 --> 06:58.580
Success, indeed.

06:58.580 --> 07:00.000
Car's coming soon.

07:00.000 --> 07:01.460
Um, are you
coming on the plane

07:01.460 --> 07:03.080
or are you just
magic traveling there?

07:04.420 --> 07:07.040
Your sister sure
loves Christmas.

07:07.040 --> 07:12.170
Oh. S-Since she was a kid,
she goes all-out.

07:12.170 --> 07:14.620
M-Maybe --
[ Clears throat ]

07:14.620 --> 07:16.880
Maybe the universe
wants you to stay here,

07:16.880 --> 07:18.540
help -- help her decorate.

07:18.540 --> 07:20.830
What? What are you
talking about?

07:20.830 --> 07:24.040
Everything is saying go to Laos.
We put the puzzle together.

07:24.040 --> 07:27.120
I know, but maybe we delay it,
just -- just a bit.

07:27.120 --> 07:29.000
Build up
your spiritual power.

07:29.000 --> 07:30.960
I feel
pretty powerful now.

07:30.960 --> 07:33.000
I mean, what more
could I learn?

07:33.000 --> 07:35.170
I mean,
can you read minds?

07:36.460 --> 07:38.170
Is that something
I'll be able to do?!

07:38.170 --> 07:39.830
-[ Gasps ]
-Well...no.

07:39.830 --> 07:41.120
Dang it!

07:41.120 --> 07:44.250
But -- Look. I worry --

07:44.250 --> 07:46.880
I worry that
you're just not ready.

07:46.880 --> 07:49.170
We're -- We're not ready.

07:49.170 --> 07:51.210
We are ready.
We're so ready.

07:51.210 --> 07:54.710
Sam bought me a plane ticket.
Tyler knows the language.

07:54.710 --> 07:57.250
I have the name
of the hotel.

07:57.250 --> 08:02.210
I mean, the universe is
practically shouting at me.

08:02.210 --> 08:06.620
And for the first time,
I know exactly what to do.

08:06.620 --> 08:10.790
♪♪

08:10.790 --> 08:12.420
Flight attendant:
Ladies and gentlemen,

08:12.420 --> 08:14.420
the captain has turned on
the "fasten seatbelt" sign.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.210
Flight attendants,
please be seated.

08:16.210 --> 08:19.080
[ Speaking Lao ]
"Where is the toilet?"

08:20.710 --> 08:25.000
Somewhere down there is
our next righteous soul.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.790
And we're gonna find him.

08:26.790 --> 08:28.750
I hope so.

08:28.750 --> 08:31.170
[ Speaking Lao ]

08:31.170 --> 08:33.290
"My companion
has been kidnapped."

08:38.790 --> 08:45.500
♪♪

08:45.500 --> 08:52.460
♪♪

08:52.460 --> 08:55.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:55.170 --> 08:56.920
[ Groans ]

09:00.960 --> 09:04.000
[ Speaking Lao ]

09:05.210 --> 09:07.040
He's so awesome, man.

09:07.040 --> 09:08.500
He wants me to be
in his wedding.

09:08.500 --> 09:10.080
I am not surprised
by that at all.

09:10.080 --> 09:11.500
Ohh!

09:11.500 --> 09:14.920
Ooh. My God!
This place is nice.

09:14.920 --> 09:16.420
[ Chuckles ]
It's not bad.

09:16.420 --> 09:19.290
Uh, hello.
Just checking in.

09:19.290 --> 09:22.460
Reservation is under
"Kevin Finn." Two N's.

09:22.460 --> 09:24.920
Welcome, Mr. Finn.
One moment.
Thank you.

09:24.920 --> 09:27.210
I'm not leaving this country
'til I try a tarantula.

09:27.210 --> 09:29.420
That sounds...awful,
but okay.

09:29.420 --> 09:31.460
I'm so sorry, Mr. Finn.

09:31.460 --> 09:33.290
I don't have a reservation
under that name.

09:33.290 --> 09:35.250
Could it be under
a different name?

09:35.250 --> 09:37.040
Uh, no,
but, um, that's --

09:37.040 --> 09:41.540
I have my confirmation
right...here.

09:41.540 --> 09:43.500
See? Kevin Finn.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.290
"2018."

09:45.290 --> 09:48.120
You made your reservation
for next year.

09:48.120 --> 09:51.210
Ohh...no.
[ Chuckles ]

09:51.210 --> 09:54.420
Um, please tell me that
you have a-a room f-for us?

09:54.420 --> 09:56.170
I'm sorry, Mr. Finn.

09:56.170 --> 09:57.750
Our hotel is booked
to capacity.

09:57.750 --> 09:59.830
No. What?

09:59.830 --> 10:02.080
Kevin?!

10:02.080 --> 10:04.120
Ben!
Wait -- What are --

10:04.120 --> 10:05.920
[ Grunting ]

10:05.920 --> 10:07.500
What are you
doing here?!

10:07.500 --> 10:08.750
I'm on my honeymoon!

10:08.750 --> 10:11.620
Y-You are?

10:11.620 --> 10:14.380
Well, I mean, it was
supposed to be our honeymoon.
Right.

10:14.380 --> 10:16.880
But since Deb and I split up and
the trip was already paid for,

10:16.880 --> 10:18.380
I decided to come
by myself.

10:18.380 --> 10:20.880
-Alright!
-A "me-moon"! Nice!

10:20.880 --> 10:23.540
Oh. This is, uh, Tyler.
Tyler, Ben.

10:23.540 --> 10:27.920
I cannot believe that
I ran into you. In Laos.

10:27.920 --> 10:29.500
Are you guys staying
at this hotel?

10:29.500 --> 10:32.670
Uh, we had a little, uh,
reservation snafu.

10:32.670 --> 10:34.000
We're working on it.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.500
Oh, my God.

10:35.500 --> 10:38.960
My suite is humongous.
Stay with me.

10:40.500 --> 10:43.210
Oh, no, w-we don't want to
interrupt your me-moon. It's --

10:43.210 --> 10:46.620
You're staying.
Let's go. [ Laughs ]

10:46.620 --> 10:47.790
Are y--

10:47.790 --> 10:51.170
♪♪

10:51.170 --> 10:53.540
-So fancy!
-[ Laughs ]

10:53.540 --> 10:54.830
Ben:
It's good, right?

10:54.830 --> 10:58.920
The bathroom is sick --
heated toilet seats.

10:58.920 --> 11:01.580
-Stop it.
-I can't.

11:01.580 --> 11:04.750
[ Kevin laughs ]

11:04.750 --> 11:08.710
Ben, this is so nice
of you. Thanks.

11:08.710 --> 11:11.920
You kidding me?
You saved my life, man.

11:11.920 --> 11:14.170
I was married to someone
who didn't love me.

11:14.170 --> 11:15.670
I deserve better.

11:15.670 --> 11:17.120
[ Chuckles ]

11:17.120 --> 11:19.040
I have never seen
so many soaps.

11:19.040 --> 11:20.920
I love this place!

11:20.920 --> 11:22.540
Okay, you guys make
yourselves at home.

11:22.540 --> 11:23.750
I'm gonna get
a quick workout in.
Alright.

11:23.750 --> 11:25.380
[ Chuckles ]

11:25.380 --> 11:27.500
Ohh!

11:27.500 --> 11:29.120
Ohh.

11:32.420 --> 11:35.000
I think
I know this tiger.

11:35.000 --> 11:36.620
Ben:
Oh, it's cool, right?

11:36.620 --> 11:38.580
It's supposed to be
the best tour in town.

11:38.580 --> 11:40.250
Going tomorrow morning.

11:40.250 --> 11:41.670
Hey, you guys should come.

11:41.670 --> 11:44.120
Ye-- Count us in!

11:44.120 --> 11:47.250
Man on TV:
Nowhere in the world

11:47.250 --> 11:49.960
will you find a destination
that is culturally...
Mmm.

11:49.960 --> 11:51.710
...and spiritually
satisfying...
What are you doing?

11:51.710 --> 11:55.330
Well, I had a bath...

11:55.330 --> 11:57.750
used the heated toilet.

11:57.750 --> 12:00.120
Uh, fun fact -- not as great
as you might think.

12:00.120 --> 12:03.380
And now I'm relaxing with
some filmed entertainment.

12:03.380 --> 12:06.500
Which is not of
an adult nature,

12:06.500 --> 12:08.710
because they don't
have that at this hotel.

12:08.710 --> 12:10.580
Because I checked.

12:10.580 --> 12:13.880
You came all this way
just to -- just to sit here?

12:13.880 --> 12:16.460
If there's a righteous soul
out there, go find it!

12:16.460 --> 12:18.920
I will.
Tomorrow, on the tour.

12:18.920 --> 12:21.330
Look.

12:21.330 --> 12:23.420
Look at the pictures
in this brochure.

12:23.420 --> 12:25.920
Half of them are from
visions that I've had.

12:25.920 --> 12:29.920
I am exactly where the
universe wants me to be.

12:29.920 --> 12:32.790
The universe wants you in a
hotel suite watching not-porn?

12:32.790 --> 12:35.250
No money for tickets?
Sam gives me miles.

12:35.250 --> 12:37.540
Screw up
the hotel reservation?

12:37.540 --> 12:41.380
Oh, Ben has a suite
at the exact same hotel.

12:41.380 --> 12:43.710
The universe has
Kevin-proofed itself.

12:43.710 --> 12:45.580
I can't fail.

12:45.580 --> 12:50.750
♪♪

12:50.750 --> 12:53.380
Why do you go all-out decorating
your house for Christmas?

12:53.380 --> 12:54.620
You live in the
middle of nowhere.

12:54.620 --> 12:57.210
I mean, no one sees it.

12:57.210 --> 12:59.040
-Only one person matters.
-Who?

12:59.040 --> 13:02.120
-Santa!
-Right. Santa.

13:02.120 --> 13:03.500
She gets
the weather forecast

13:03.500 --> 13:05.290
from the National
Weather Service.

13:05.290 --> 13:06.790
Yes, I do,
to accurately predict

13:06.790 --> 13:08.500
the sleigh trajectory
on our roof.

13:08.500 --> 13:10.120
Hmm.

13:10.120 --> 13:11.670
And I have updated
my formula

13:11.670 --> 13:13.380
to include the wind gusts
that are to be expected.

13:13.380 --> 13:15.170
No, no, no.
No -- No math, please.

13:15.170 --> 13:16.380
-No math.
-Okay.

13:16.380 --> 13:19.080
-Uh, Amy? Hey!
-Iggy!

13:19.080 --> 13:20.750
-Hi.
-Hello. [ Laughs ]

13:20.750 --> 13:22.710
-You're here!
-I'm here.

13:22.710 --> 13:25.040
The -- Um, w-well, hi.
It's good to see you.

13:25.040 --> 13:26.580
You too.

13:26.580 --> 13:28.540
This is Reese, my -- my --
This is my daughter, Reese.

13:28.540 --> 13:30.040
-Hi.
-Yeah.

13:30.040 --> 13:32.290
Oh. Hi. Uh, your mom has
told me a lot about you.

13:32.290 --> 13:34.380
-[ Chuckles ]
-[ Clears throat ]

13:34.380 --> 13:37.000
Oh, um, this is Nate.
This is my friend Nate.

13:37.000 --> 13:39.580
He's helping me with a project.
For Santa.

13:39.580 --> 13:41.580
For the house.
For Christmas!

13:41.580 --> 13:43.210
Hi. How are you?

13:43.210 --> 13:45.210
-Good to meet you, man.
-You too.

13:45.210 --> 13:47.620
So, uh, listen, I'm heading
out of town for the holidays.

13:47.620 --> 13:49.380
Yeah.

13:49.380 --> 13:51.460
Thought maybe we could get
together if you're free or...?

13:51.460 --> 13:52.620
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

13:52.620 --> 13:55.170
Yeah. Uh-huh. Yeah.

13:55.170 --> 13:56.880
That sounds --
That sounds great.

13:56.880 --> 13:59.460
Uh, excuse me. I'm gonna use
the restroom, let you guys talk.

13:59.460 --> 14:00.920
Okay.

14:00.920 --> 14:04.210
Reese, did you, uh, need
to go to the restroom?

14:04.210 --> 14:06.380
No.

14:07.790 --> 14:09.420
Okay. Okay, great.

14:09.420 --> 14:10.830
Okay.

14:10.830 --> 14:13.460
♪ It's Christmas ♪

14:13.460 --> 14:15.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:15.620 --> 14:19.750
Food on sticks, guys!
That is the perfect way to eat.

14:19.750 --> 14:21.790
This is exactly
like I remember it.

14:21.790 --> 14:24.710
-It's amazing.
-You've been here?

14:24.710 --> 14:26.790
-I-I saw a documentary.
-Oh.

14:26.790 --> 14:28.540
About this market.

14:28.540 --> 14:30.170
Come on.
Bus leaves in five.

14:30.170 --> 14:31.580
Hmm.

14:31.580 --> 14:34.540
Here you go.
Three all-day passes.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.120
-Three?
-Yeah.

14:37.620 --> 14:39.040
Where's Tyler?

14:39.040 --> 14:41.250
[ Sighs ] Tyler.
Um...

14:41.250 --> 14:43.580
Okay. Go on.
I'll get him.

14:43.580 --> 14:46.170
-Okay. Save you seats.
-Alright.

14:46.170 --> 14:49.170
Tyler! Ty!

14:49.170 --> 14:50.790
[ Grunts ] Sorry.

14:50.790 --> 14:52.120
Excuse me.

14:52.120 --> 14:55.080
Oh! Sorry.
I'm so sorry.

14:55.080 --> 14:57.170
-Thank you.
-No problem.

14:57.170 --> 14:58.540
You a tourist?
You need something?

14:58.540 --> 14:59.670
I can get you anything.

14:59.670 --> 15:01.420
No. I'm -- I'm good.
Thanks. Tyler!

15:01.420 --> 15:03.620
Place to eat? I know
the best noodles in town.

15:03.620 --> 15:06.580
Uh, money changer?
Finest silk? Anything!

15:06.580 --> 15:07.920
I'm just looking
for a friend.

15:07.920 --> 15:09.250
I can get you a friend.

15:09.250 --> 15:11.000
No, no. No.
Just no, thank you.

15:11.000 --> 15:13.000
-Tyler!
-Tyler!

15:13.000 --> 15:14.880
I really, really don't
need your help, okay?

15:14.880 --> 15:17.210
Okay, boss. Tyler!

15:17.210 --> 15:18.710
Aah!

15:18.710 --> 15:20.460
[ Whimpers ]

15:21.540 --> 15:22.750
Hey, man!

15:25.040 --> 15:27.290
Think I can get this
on carry-on?

15:27.290 --> 15:29.790
Where the hell
did you get that?

15:29.790 --> 15:31.250
Oh, they're all over
the place.

15:31.250 --> 15:32.960
It's for the
Laos new year!

15:32.960 --> 15:35.710
Oh! And snacks.

15:35.710 --> 15:37.380
They're water beetles.

15:37.380 --> 15:40.000
They look gross,
but they taste gross, too.

15:40.000 --> 15:43.170
Ew. Oh, the bus!
The bus!

15:43.170 --> 15:45.920
No, no, no, no! No!
Wait! Wait!

15:45.920 --> 15:47.620
[ Sighs ]

15:47.620 --> 15:49.460
Oh, man.

15:49.460 --> 15:52.420
I'm sorry, buddy.
This is my fault.

15:52.420 --> 15:53.880
It -- Ohh.
[ Crunch ]

15:53.880 --> 15:55.670
Wow!

15:55.670 --> 15:57.170
That does not get better.

15:57.170 --> 16:00.120
We need to
get on that bus.

16:00.120 --> 16:03.080
[ Brakes squeal ]

16:03.080 --> 16:06.290
-You need a ride?
-[ Sighs ]

16:11.290 --> 16:13.540
Kevin: Where is the bus?
I don't see it.

16:13.540 --> 16:16.330
Don't worry. Those tour buses
always stop at the same sites.

16:16.330 --> 16:17.580
We'll catch them
at the next stop.

16:17.580 --> 16:19.040
Gum?

16:19.040 --> 16:21.080
-Oh. Thanks.
-$4 a stick.

16:21.080 --> 16:22.210
Worth it.

16:22.210 --> 16:23.670
-Hey, no, no, no. Whoa.
-Hey, hey!

16:23.670 --> 16:25.960
We're already paying you a lot
of money to catch that tour bus,

16:25.960 --> 16:27.080
which you are failing at.

16:27.080 --> 16:28.420
Why are you gouging us?

16:28.420 --> 16:31.040
I have a baby on the way
any day now, man.

16:31.040 --> 16:33.670
You have any idea how much
that's gonna cost me?

16:33.670 --> 16:35.080
You have kids?

16:35.080 --> 16:38.420
Not yet. But I plan on having
a massive family one day.

16:38.420 --> 16:40.330
Three boys, two girls.

16:40.330 --> 16:42.960
Juan's the oldest.
Then Barbara the bookish one.

16:42.960 --> 16:45.170
Mark's the middle kid.
We got to keep an eye on him.

16:45.170 --> 16:46.670
Alison's next.

16:46.670 --> 16:49.170
Then little Teddy,
our youngest.

16:49.170 --> 16:51.080
[ Chuckles ]
That scamp.

16:53.380 --> 16:56.120
I haven't thought about it
as much as him.

16:56.120 --> 16:58.540
Well, think hard
before you do it.

16:58.540 --> 17:00.290
Food, clothes, school.

17:00.290 --> 17:02.750
I'm trying
everything I can.

17:02.750 --> 17:05.290
Me and my wife are barely
staying ahead on rent as it is.

17:05.290 --> 17:06.960
Well, there's
plenty more of this

17:06.960 --> 17:08.250
if you catch up
with that bus.

17:10.000 --> 17:11.580
I got you, baby.

17:11.580 --> 17:13.380
[ Gears grinding ]

17:13.380 --> 17:15.040
-What is that?
-Oh, no.

17:15.040 --> 17:17.380
-What's happening?
-No, no, no, no, no.

17:17.380 --> 17:19.670
[ Creaking ]

17:19.670 --> 17:21.500
[ Hissing ]

17:21.500 --> 17:29.670
♪♪

17:29.670 --> 17:31.170
[ Tyler groans ]

17:33.880 --> 17:36.380
-Minor setback.
-Ahh.

17:36.380 --> 17:37.710
We'll catch up with the bus
at the next stop.

17:37.710 --> 17:39.460
Well, what do we do?

17:39.460 --> 17:42.620
This is a tourist spot.
Be a tourist.

17:42.620 --> 17:44.540
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:51.380 --> 17:53.580
Still think the universe
has got your back?

17:53.580 --> 17:56.250
Yeah, I mean, we'll --
we'll be on the road

17:56.250 --> 17:59.750
as soon as Vong
gets the car fixed.

17:59.750 --> 18:02.500
Which should be...

18:02.500 --> 18:04.210
soon.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
I could do it.
I could, um...

18:10.000 --> 18:13.040
I could start that car.

18:13.040 --> 18:15.380
Yeah, definitely
you could do that.

18:15.380 --> 18:16.790
I -- [ Sighs ]

18:16.790 --> 18:18.710
I don't interfere because
it's the height of hubris

18:18.710 --> 18:21.330
to circumvent the will
of the universe,

18:21.330 --> 18:24.540
the will of God,
but I could do it.

18:24.540 --> 18:26.500
It's -- It's an
emergency, right?

18:26.500 --> 18:28.580
Right.

18:30.750 --> 18:32.460
If you --

18:32.460 --> 18:35.080
If you tell me to do it,

18:35.080 --> 18:36.880
I will.

18:39.380 --> 18:42.210
Um...

18:48.540 --> 18:50.500
Don't fix the car.
Don't do a thing.

18:50.500 --> 18:52.210
Why?

18:52.210 --> 18:53.330
[ Chuckles ]

18:56.460 --> 18:59.250
That's from my vision.

18:59.250 --> 19:00.790
That car broke down
for a reason.

19:00.790 --> 19:02.830
We're here for a reason!

19:02.830 --> 19:05.250
How can you be sure?

19:05.250 --> 19:08.080
I've trusted you,
your -- your lessons,

19:08.080 --> 19:09.830
your guidance
for this whole ride.

19:09.830 --> 19:11.290
And it's gotten us here.

19:11.290 --> 19:14.000
Can you just
trust me now?

19:14.000 --> 19:21.790
♪♪

19:21.790 --> 19:23.830
[ Clinking ]

19:23.830 --> 19:30.380
♪♪

19:30.380 --> 19:34.040
So, what do you, um --
What do you think of Iggy?

19:34.040 --> 19:36.670
Mom, I'm not
talking about this.

19:36.670 --> 19:38.120
-Wha--
-It's weird.

19:38.120 --> 19:41.960
It's not weird.
Come on.

19:41.960 --> 19:43.330
Give me somethin'.

19:43.330 --> 19:45.880
He seems nice, I guess.

19:45.880 --> 19:47.670
Hm. Nate didn't seem
to like him.

19:47.670 --> 19:49.500
Couldn't get out of there
quick enough.

19:49.500 --> 19:52.500
-That was strange, huh?
-Yeah.

19:52.500 --> 19:54.880
Am I crazy? Was I the only one
that noticed that?

19:56.460 --> 19:58.330
What?

19:58.330 --> 20:01.750
Nate likes you. Okay?

20:01.750 --> 20:04.920
That's why he was
acting stupid.

20:06.500 --> 20:09.960
Uh. Uh.
[ Chuckles

20:09.960 --> 20:13.500
Wha-- Uh, how do you
even know this?

20:13.500 --> 20:15.290
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:15.290 --> 20:18.040
Because...

20:18.040 --> 20:19.790
he -- he wanted to know
if I was okay

20:19.790 --> 20:21.210
if h-he asked you out.

20:23.330 --> 20:24.830
Well, what did you say?

20:24.830 --> 20:26.380
No.

20:28.580 --> 20:30.580
Reese.

20:30.580 --> 20:32.880
Honey, you know that I'm gonna
always love your dad.

20:32.880 --> 20:34.580
Mom, that's not why.

20:34.580 --> 20:37.250
Well, then why then?

20:37.250 --> 20:39.290
Because you're not ready.

20:39.290 --> 20:41.750
I'm ready. I'm --

20:41.750 --> 20:43.960
I'm...very ready.

20:43.960 --> 20:45.670
Why would you say
that I wasn't ready?

20:45.670 --> 20:47.460
Because of that.

20:52.880 --> 20:55.880
You haven't taken it off
since Dad died.

20:55.880 --> 21:01.790
♪♪

21:01.790 --> 21:03.880
[ Engine sputters ]

21:03.880 --> 21:06.040
Okay! Cut it!

21:07.670 --> 21:10.460
Sorry, guys.
It's not happening.

21:10.460 --> 21:13.290
We can walk to town,
and I'll get a tow to
come back for the car.

21:13.290 --> 21:16.380
[ Sighs ]
Here's your money back.

21:16.380 --> 21:18.290
Oh, no, Vong.
I'm -- I'm -- I'm good.

21:18.290 --> 21:20.330
I'm not taking it.
I-I-I like it here.

21:20.330 --> 21:22.620
I want to --
I want to stay for a little bit.

21:22.620 --> 21:24.500
Well, I'm going.

21:24.500 --> 21:26.670
Don't waste your time here,
Kevin.

21:26.670 --> 21:29.080
You -- You need to try and
find the soul another way.

21:29.080 --> 21:30.290
[ Trunk closes ]

21:30.290 --> 21:33.250
You can stay or come.
Up to you.

21:37.120 --> 21:39.290
It's you!
[ Laughs excitedly ]

21:39.290 --> 21:41.580
-What?
-Kevin, wait. I --

21:41.580 --> 21:43.460
This is it.

21:43.460 --> 21:45.750
Vong: What -- What --
What's happening?

21:45.750 --> 21:53.460
♪♪

21:57.040 --> 21:58.460
-Hey, man.
-Hey.

21:58.460 --> 21:59.750
What's up?

21:59.750 --> 22:01.330
Well, I don't know.

22:01.330 --> 22:05.040
Did -- Did you
feel anything?

22:05.040 --> 22:06.920
No.

22:06.920 --> 22:08.670
Huh. [ Chuckles ]

22:10.500 --> 22:13.830
Uh, okay.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.710
Can I get
one of those?

22:20.670 --> 22:23.250
-That's good stuff.
-[ Laughs ]

22:27.210 --> 22:29.420
Something should happen
when I anoint someone, right?

22:29.420 --> 22:32.540
I mean, I-I should
have felt something.

22:32.540 --> 22:36.080
I would think so.

22:36.080 --> 22:38.920
What the hell
is going on? I --

22:38.920 --> 22:40.710
What is the universe
trying to tell me?

22:42.330 --> 22:44.790
I don't think the universe
was talking to you.

22:44.790 --> 22:48.500
That -- That message
was meant for me.

22:50.460 --> 22:52.710
You? What's the universe
trying to tell you?

22:52.710 --> 22:55.290
That -- That I'm wrong.

22:55.290 --> 22:57.210
That...

22:57.210 --> 23:00.080
That there are no other
righteous souls.

23:00.080 --> 23:01.880
[ Chuckles softly ]

23:01.880 --> 23:03.710
What?

23:03.710 --> 23:10.710
♪♪

23:18.040 --> 23:20.380
Okay. Let's just take
a deep breath and strategize.

23:20.380 --> 23:21.880
Strategize what?

23:21.880 --> 23:24.670
Um, our next move?

23:24.670 --> 23:29.170
Kevin, there are
no other righteous.

23:29.170 --> 23:31.540
[ Sighs ]
How do you know that?

23:31.540 --> 23:35.290
Because we just saw it.
This was all for nothing.

23:35.290 --> 23:38.210
I convinced
35 celestial beings

23:38.210 --> 23:40.210
to give up paradise
for a fool's errand!

23:40.210 --> 23:41.670
I ruined their lives!

23:44.880 --> 23:46.460
I ruined your life.

23:46.460 --> 23:47.620
-No, you didn't.
-Kevin.

23:47.620 --> 23:49.380
You didn't.

23:49.380 --> 23:51.830
Go home.

23:51.830 --> 23:54.080
Go back to your family.

23:55.500 --> 23:57.670
What are you gonna do?

24:02.580 --> 24:04.380
I don't know.

24:05.880 --> 24:08.330
I'm still righteous, right?
I mean, you --

24:08.330 --> 24:10.460
You were right
about that.

24:11.670 --> 24:13.830
Yes.

24:13.830 --> 24:16.290
You're the only one left.

24:18.120 --> 24:21.250
Well, maybe I'm enough.

24:21.250 --> 24:27.080
♪♪

24:27.080 --> 24:29.290
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:29.290 --> 24:34.750
♪♪

24:34.750 --> 24:36.790
[ Woman speaking Lao ]

24:36.790 --> 24:38.620
[ Speaking Lao ]

24:38.620 --> 24:41.170
Oh, I -- What is it?

24:41.170 --> 24:42.790
[ Speaking Lao ]

24:42.790 --> 24:44.540
-Ahh.
-Mmm!

24:45.670 --> 24:48.120
Oh, my God!

24:48.120 --> 24:51.960
This is the most delicious...
mystery food I've ever tasted!

24:51.960 --> 24:53.500
[ Laughs ]

24:53.500 --> 24:55.170
Mmm!

24:55.170 --> 24:57.420
You are...a weird man.
[ Laughs ]

24:57.420 --> 24:58.960
Yeah.

24:58.960 --> 25:00.920
But a good man.

25:00.920 --> 25:03.330
Thank you. I-I try.

25:03.330 --> 25:04.750
Ohh!

25:04.750 --> 25:06.960
Oh. [ Speaking Lao ]

25:06.960 --> 25:09.120
[ Cellphone clicking, chiming ]

25:09.120 --> 25:11.620
Thank you very much.

25:11.620 --> 25:15.170
♪♪

25:15.170 --> 25:17.170
Hey.

25:17.170 --> 25:18.880
How's the car?

25:18.880 --> 25:21.120
Waiting for
the tow truck.

25:21.120 --> 25:23.750
After that,
I don't know what to do.

25:25.040 --> 25:27.790
Well, maybe I could help.

25:27.790 --> 25:31.380
♪♪

25:31.380 --> 25:32.920
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

25:32.920 --> 25:34.250
Can I get you
anything else?

25:34.250 --> 25:36.710
No, I'm -- I'm fine.
Thanks.

25:38.710 --> 25:40.250
Tyler: Hey!

25:40.250 --> 25:42.790
We got
the same drink!

25:42.790 --> 25:45.960
Mind if I join you?

25:47.750 --> 25:51.040
Oh, I-I don't think I'd be
good company right now.

25:51.040 --> 25:53.040
That's not possible.

25:56.750 --> 25:58.540
What's got you down?

26:00.420 --> 26:01.960
Work problems.

26:01.960 --> 26:04.290
Hm. That bad?

26:04.290 --> 26:07.880
Bad enough that
I threw in the towel

26:07.880 --> 26:09.960
and now here I am.

26:09.960 --> 26:12.580
Well, I'm glad
you're here.

26:12.580 --> 26:15.380
It's always nice to
meet another American.

26:15.380 --> 26:19.830
Oh. [ Coughs ] Oh.
Um, I'm not from there.

26:19.830 --> 26:21.380
Ah. Canadian, eh?

26:21.380 --> 26:23.120
[ Chuckles ]

26:23.120 --> 26:24.380
Sure.

26:24.380 --> 26:26.330
Rad. I love poutine.

26:26.330 --> 26:28.960
Are you always
this happy?

26:28.960 --> 26:31.210
Well, I'm drinking
a fruity cocktail,

26:31.210 --> 26:33.000
sitting next to
a beautiful lady.

26:33.000 --> 26:34.380
Why wouldn't I be happy?

26:36.040 --> 26:38.750
Oh, hey,
just share mine.

26:38.750 --> 26:43.170
♪♪

26:43.170 --> 26:45.710
Thank you, Betty.
Appreciate you.

26:45.710 --> 26:47.380
[ Chuckles ] Oh!

26:47.380 --> 26:50.170
-Nate. Hi.
-Hey.

26:50.170 --> 26:54.040
Hey. Uh, just here for
a cup of coffee. Me. I am.

26:54.040 --> 26:56.080
-You have yours.
-Yeah.

26:56.080 --> 26:58.380
-Yeah.
-I have an extra if you...

26:58.380 --> 27:00.880
That guy [Clears throat]
that you met,

27:00.880 --> 27:04.830
he's, um, a professor that
I went out on a date with.

27:04.830 --> 27:06.830
A-A date date.

27:06.830 --> 27:09.580
Oh. Yeah, okay.

27:09.580 --> 27:11.750
But -- Um...

27:11.750 --> 27:15.580
But I realized that, um,

27:15.580 --> 27:18.580
I'm just not ready
to date yet, so...

27:18.580 --> 27:20.290
It's cool, right?

27:20.290 --> 27:23.290
That I-I realized that
with him,

27:23.290 --> 27:26.210
and, you know,
not while I was out

27:26.210 --> 27:28.420
on a date with
another person.

27:28.420 --> 27:30.540
Yeah, yeah, I know
exactly how you feel.

27:30.540 --> 27:33.540
You know, post-divorce, who
wants to hop into something?

27:33.540 --> 27:35.710
That's why it's important
to have friends.

27:35.710 --> 27:37.290
Right.
To get you through
all the rough patches.

27:37.290 --> 27:39.080
-Yes! So true.
-Right.

27:39.080 --> 27:41.960
True, true, true.
So true.

27:41.960 --> 27:43.750
[ Both chuckle ]

27:43.750 --> 27:46.080
[ Chuckles ]

27:46.080 --> 27:47.960
Okay, well, thank you.
Um...

27:47.960 --> 27:49.830
Thanks for making that

27:49.830 --> 27:52.460
a lot less awkward
than I tried to make it.

27:52.460 --> 27:53.830
-You're welcome.
-Okay.

27:53.830 --> 27:55.500
Ah, well, you know what?

27:55.500 --> 27:57.880
I will take you up on that extra
cup of coffee, so thank you.

27:57.880 --> 27:59.790
Uh, that one's creamer.

27:59.790 --> 28:02.750
Oh, my gosh. Yeah.
That is creamer. Ooh!

28:02.750 --> 28:04.120
-[ Laughs ]
-It's very creamy.

28:04.120 --> 28:05.710
-I am so sorry.
-And not at all what I expected.

28:05.710 --> 28:08.000
No. I shouldn't have
chugged it like that.

28:08.000 --> 28:09.830
That's the one you want.
My bad.

28:09.830 --> 28:11.880
[ Laughs ]
I'm so sorry.

28:11.880 --> 28:15.670
This is the third time this
month that car broke down.

28:15.670 --> 28:18.290
The repairs are costing more
than what the car is worth.

28:18.290 --> 28:19.830
It's gonna be okay.
We'll figure it out.

28:19.830 --> 28:21.710
I can't even
take care of myself.

28:21.710 --> 28:25.210
How can I be responsible
for another life?

28:28.290 --> 28:31.000
Feels like the weight
of the whole world

28:31.000 --> 28:32.620
is on your shoulders?

28:32.620 --> 28:34.580
Yes.

28:34.580 --> 28:36.670
Yeah, I-I-I get that.

28:36.670 --> 28:38.790
Uh, in --

28:38.790 --> 28:41.960
In my, um, job,

28:41.960 --> 28:44.460
there is
a ton of pressure.

28:44.460 --> 28:48.000
But I've had to learn
to ignore the fact

28:48.000 --> 28:52.580
that everything will
fall apart if I fail.

28:54.580 --> 28:58.920
How can you do that when
everything is so overwhelming?

28:58.920 --> 29:03.670
Well, uh, by taking it
just one step at a time

29:03.670 --> 29:06.580
and -- and hoping that it makes
a difference in the end.

29:06.580 --> 29:10.500
Y-You focus on the things
that you can control

29:10.500 --> 29:13.830
because everything else
is just gonna happen

29:13.830 --> 29:15.500
no matter what you do.

29:18.330 --> 29:20.620
I don't know.
It -- It helps me.

29:20.620 --> 29:22.790
Thanks.

29:25.330 --> 29:27.670
Sound like you have
a very important job.

29:27.670 --> 29:30.830
-Oh. [ Chuckles ]
-What do you do?

29:30.830 --> 29:35.670
Uh, I-I'm a, uh, uh...

29:35.670 --> 29:37.210
senator.

29:37.210 --> 29:38.880
Wow!

29:38.880 --> 29:40.880
[ Cellphone rings ]

29:40.880 --> 29:43.540
Oh.

29:43.540 --> 29:45.880
It's my wife.

29:45.880 --> 29:47.250
Hello?

29:48.880 --> 29:51.040
[ Speaking Lao ]

29:57.210 --> 29:59.380
[ Cellphone locks ]
My wife is in labor.

29:59.380 --> 30:02.170
I need to get home now!

30:02.170 --> 30:04.120
Yep.

30:04.120 --> 30:06.960
So the Postmates guy
shows up,

30:06.960 --> 30:10.170
and I notice he'd eaten
half my bag of grapes.

30:10.170 --> 30:11.580
Oh, so rude!

30:11.580 --> 30:13.380
What'd you do?

30:13.380 --> 30:15.620
Well, we bonded over
how delicious grapes were,

30:15.620 --> 30:17.460
and then I gave him the rest
of the bag for the ride home.

30:17.460 --> 30:22.080
[ Man speaking Lao ]

30:22.080 --> 30:25.040
I think he just said
this is it.

30:25.040 --> 30:27.960
[ Mariachi band
plays slow song ]
Would you care to dance?

30:27.960 --> 30:30.540
Sure. That'd be nice.

30:30.540 --> 30:33.580
Are you feeling
any better?

30:33.580 --> 30:35.040
For now.

30:35.040 --> 30:38.080
But as soon as the song is over
and reality sets in,

30:38.080 --> 30:41.670
I'm gonna -- I'm gonna want
to fade away and disappear.

30:41.670 --> 30:44.170
Oh, that's not how the
universe works, though.

30:44.170 --> 30:47.460
Oh. Well, how does
the universe work?

30:47.460 --> 30:49.250
In -- In your opinion?

30:49.250 --> 30:53.330
There's no disappearing.
The world's too small.

30:53.330 --> 30:56.670
Friends will always find you
when you need them.

30:56.670 --> 30:58.000
I mean, look at us.

30:58.000 --> 31:00.000
Who would think that
an American and a Canadian

31:00.000 --> 31:04.040
would be dancing to
a mariachi band in Laos?

31:04.040 --> 31:06.920
It's amazing.

31:08.830 --> 31:10.540
Wait. Wha--

31:10.540 --> 31:13.290
That's a mariachi band?!

31:18.670 --> 31:20.290
Do you want to go
over there and look?

31:20.290 --> 31:21.960
Hi. Excuse me, sir.
We need a taxi right away.

31:21.960 --> 31:23.420
-It's an emergency.
-Kevin.

31:23.420 --> 31:25.170
I can't talk right now, really.
Oh, great! Vong! Taxi!

31:25.170 --> 31:26.620
No! Oh, sir, please!
We need it!

31:26.620 --> 31:28.040
Kevin, listen to me!

31:28.040 --> 31:29.500
Don't worry, Vong.
We'll get a taxi.

31:29.500 --> 31:31.210
We'll get a taxi.
We're gonna need one more taxi.

31:31.210 --> 31:33.120
Kevin!
Please!
Hey. What's going on?

31:33.120 --> 31:35.120
Tyler, Vong's wife is in labor,
and we need a ride.

31:35.120 --> 31:36.920
-Can you --
-Uh, taxi!

31:36.920 --> 31:38.420
Kevin.

31:38.420 --> 31:39.960
Yvette, I really need to
concentrate right now!

31:39.960 --> 31:41.670
[ Tires screech ]

31:41.670 --> 31:43.380
What was that?

31:45.040 --> 31:46.330
Mariachi.

31:46.330 --> 31:48.210
Mariachi?!

31:48.210 --> 31:49.960
Mariachi!

31:49.960 --> 31:51.170
You still think this was
all for nothing?

31:51.170 --> 31:54.040
Hmnh! [ Gasps ]

31:54.040 --> 31:55.540
Uh, can you guys
give us a ride?

31:57.620 --> 31:59.920
Amy: Oh, my God.
What's going on?

32:01.750 --> 32:03.750
I hope that's nothing bad.

32:03.750 --> 32:06.500
Maybe Mrs. Glubo forgot
to put on clothes again.

32:06.500 --> 32:07.710
Reese.

32:07.710 --> 32:09.960
What? That happened.

32:09.960 --> 32:13.290
She is in a home now.

32:13.290 --> 32:15.670
Amy: Is that Nate?

32:15.670 --> 32:21.670
♪♪

32:21.670 --> 32:27.380
♪♪

32:27.380 --> 32:29.500
Amy: What happened?

32:29.500 --> 32:31.210
Maybe there was a gas leak
in the neighborhood.

32:31.210 --> 32:33.330
Oh, my God. Really?

32:33.330 --> 32:35.500
Or maybe it was
a Christmas travesty

32:35.500 --> 32:38.210
no one was seeing
Santa's landing pad.

32:41.670 --> 32:44.880
Did you --
Did you do all this

32:44.880 --> 32:47.580
so people would
pass by my house?

32:47.580 --> 32:49.330
Who knows.

32:49.330 --> 32:51.920
Well, except Santa.
He knows everything.

32:55.210 --> 32:57.330
And, uh, maybe
you should get inside,

32:57.330 --> 33:00.670
you know, in case
the gas leak spreads.

33:00.670 --> 33:01.830
[ Chuckles ]

33:01.830 --> 33:05.080
♪♪

33:05.080 --> 33:08.380
Kevin: It is crazy
how things work out.

33:08.380 --> 33:10.580
You have no clue.

33:12.500 --> 33:14.920
Are you okay, Ty?

33:14.920 --> 33:18.830
Okay? I'm more okay
than I've ever been.

33:18.830 --> 33:22.210
I met the most
amazing woman.

33:22.210 --> 33:23.750
Really? Where?

33:23.750 --> 33:25.580
The hotel bar.

33:25.580 --> 33:28.330
It was, like,
everything dimmed

33:28.330 --> 33:30.330
except for her
across the room.

33:30.330 --> 33:32.000
Well, did you
t-talk to her?

33:32.000 --> 33:33.880
We talked.

33:33.880 --> 33:36.250
-Aww!
-We danced.

33:36.250 --> 33:41.000
For a brief moment,
we just...were.

33:41.000 --> 33:43.000
Ohh!

33:43.000 --> 33:44.080
Did you get
her number?

33:44.080 --> 33:45.670
I didn't even
get her name.

33:45.670 --> 33:48.080
Well, maybe
we can find her.

33:48.080 --> 33:51.000
What'd she --
What'd she look like?

33:51.000 --> 33:52.460
[ Sighs ]

33:52.460 --> 33:56.170
Beautiful brown eyes.
Flawless brown skin.

33:56.170 --> 33:58.790
Her hair was braided
in a ring

33:58.790 --> 34:01.000
like...a halo.

34:04.540 --> 34:06.460
Huh. Wow.

34:06.460 --> 34:10.290
Um, what was she wearing?

34:10.290 --> 34:12.460
She was wearing
this beautiful shirt.

34:12.460 --> 34:17.210
It was the color of
a beautiful orange bird.

34:17.210 --> 34:19.670
Red dangling earrings

34:19.670 --> 34:23.250
made out of this,
like, poofy tassel.

34:25.380 --> 34:26.960
I met an angel, Kev.

34:26.960 --> 34:28.540
[ Brakes squeal ]
Mm-hmm.

34:28.540 --> 34:29.880
And I don't know
what to do.

34:29.880 --> 34:33.170
Hey! We're here!

34:33.170 --> 34:35.620
Vong: Vatsana!

34:35.620 --> 34:39.580
Vatsana! Vatsana!
Vatsana!

34:39.580 --> 34:41.330
[ Speaking Lao ]

34:41.330 --> 34:44.210
[ Speaking Lao ]

34:46.250 --> 34:48.080
She said she called
ambulance an hour ago.

34:48.080 --> 34:50.250
[ Vatsana screaming ]

34:50.250 --> 34:52.540
[ Speaking Lao ]

34:52.540 --> 34:54.330
She thinks she's gonna
have the baby now!

34:54.330 --> 34:55.830
-Wha--
-What do I do?!

34:55.830 --> 34:57.290
Uh, just keep
talking to her.

34:57.290 --> 34:59.290
Uh, you'll talk us
through this, right?

34:59.290 --> 35:00.670
Don't look at me.

35:00.670 --> 35:02.540
What? This is what
the universe wants.

35:02.540 --> 35:03.670
What if I mess up?

35:03.670 --> 35:07.080
Hey, Kev, can I be
of assistance?

35:07.080 --> 35:08.580
You know how
to deliver a baby?

35:08.580 --> 35:11.000
Lucille:
Not him, numb-nuts. Me!

35:11.000 --> 35:13.170
-Lucille's a midwife.
-What?

35:13.170 --> 35:15.330
Now, do you need me
to describe the female anatomy,

35:15.330 --> 35:16.960
or can we get to work?

35:16.960 --> 35:19.290
Hi, Lucille.
It's nice to see you.

35:23.920 --> 35:25.880
[ Breathing rhythmically ]

35:25.880 --> 35:27.750
Lucille: You're doing great,
sweetie. Just keep breathing.

35:27.750 --> 35:29.210
I'm gonna help your husband
with the baby.

35:29.210 --> 35:31.290
That's amazing!
You're amazing!

35:31.290 --> 35:33.170
Knock off the back slapping

35:33.170 --> 35:35.170
until I know you idiots haven't
crapped the bed on this!

35:35.170 --> 35:37.580
Now let's get down
to business.
Okay.

35:37.580 --> 35:40.170
People often call childbirth
the miracle of life,

35:40.170 --> 35:42.920
but to actually witness it,

35:42.920 --> 35:45.330
it's truly miraculous.

35:45.330 --> 35:47.290
So you gonna point me
toward the action or what?!

35:47.290 --> 35:50.210
Fine. It's the
miracle of life.

35:50.210 --> 35:52.670
It's the miracle of life.
It's the miracle of life.

35:52.670 --> 35:54.580
Ohh.

35:54.580 --> 35:57.790
Crap! This baby's
coming in fast and hard!

35:57.790 --> 36:00.460
-O-Okay. What do I do?!
-[ Moaning loudly ]

36:00.460 --> 36:01.880
Catch the baby, idiot!

36:01.880 --> 36:03.420
You got this, Vong.

36:03.420 --> 36:05.330
Ohh.

36:05.330 --> 36:08.540
[ Screaming ]

36:08.540 --> 36:10.210
[ Baby cries ]

36:10.210 --> 36:12.540
-Ohh!
-It's a girl!

36:12.540 --> 36:14.290
She's a girl!

36:14.290 --> 36:17.170
[ Mariachi band playing
up-tempo music ]

36:17.170 --> 36:23.290
♪♪

36:26.330 --> 36:28.290
Can you believe
that just happened?

36:28.290 --> 36:29.790
Yvette:
Hmm. [ Chuckles ]

36:29.790 --> 36:31.670
We delivered a baby.

36:31.670 --> 36:34.330
[ Chuckles ]

36:36.330 --> 36:38.540
Hey.

36:38.540 --> 36:42.670
I-I-I know we didn't accomplish
what we set out to do,

36:42.670 --> 36:47.960
but -- but we did something
amazing today.

36:47.960 --> 36:51.250
Maybe this is the
universe's way of saying

36:51.250 --> 36:55.920
that it -- it's not just about
finding the righteous.

36:55.920 --> 36:59.880
It's -- It's about...

36:59.880 --> 37:03.420
being good and...

37:03.420 --> 37:04.830
doing the right thing.

37:04.830 --> 37:08.500
And not because I-I had to.
But because I...

37:08.500 --> 37:11.080
I w-- I wanted to.

37:12.460 --> 37:15.120
I believe you're right.

37:15.120 --> 37:17.880
Would you like
to meet Laya?

37:17.880 --> 37:20.920
Laya? Yeah.

37:20.920 --> 37:22.380
[ Laya fusses ]

37:22.380 --> 37:25.500
"Beautiful one."

37:25.500 --> 37:28.120
Hi, beautiful one!

37:28.120 --> 37:30.080
[ Twinkling ]

37:30.080 --> 37:36.420
♪♪

37:36.420 --> 37:42.460
♪♪

37:42.460 --> 37:48.790
♪♪

37:48.790 --> 37:55.170
♪♪

37:55.170 --> 37:57.880
[ Overlapping voices ]

38:02.670 --> 38:04.670
Flight attendant:
Ladies and gentlemen,

38:04.670 --> 38:06.790
the captain has turned on
the "fasten seatbelt" sign.

38:06.790 --> 38:10.040
Please return to your seats and
keep your seatbelts fastened.

38:10.040 --> 38:13.250
Oh, well, hey there,
Sleeping Beauty.

38:13.250 --> 38:15.960
-What?
-You knocked out hard!

38:15.960 --> 38:17.170
Can't blame you, though.

38:17.170 --> 38:19.210
How did I get here?

38:19.210 --> 38:22.540
Dude. How indeed.

38:23.790 --> 38:26.670
We tore Laos up.

38:26.670 --> 38:29.330
I'm surprised we survived
to catch the flight home.

38:29.330 --> 38:30.790
Wait. Tyler, what are you
talking about?

38:30.790 --> 38:33.620
The last thing
I remember was...

38:33.620 --> 38:35.420
the baby.

38:35.420 --> 38:37.120
Yeah, after you
delivered that baby,

38:37.120 --> 38:39.540
you were, like,
powered up.

38:39.540 --> 38:42.210
You wanted to
experience everything.

38:42.210 --> 38:44.670
Everything? What d--
[ Cellphone unlocks ]

38:47.120 --> 38:49.040
Tha-- We --

38:51.080 --> 38:54.880
Um, a-are those marks
from a tiger?

38:54.880 --> 38:57.710
You, sir, are a badass.

38:57.710 --> 38:59.290
[ Winces ]

38:59.290 --> 39:02.460
Ah, those little guys
tickled something fierce.

39:02.460 --> 39:06.000
[ Chuckles ]
W-What's that?

39:06.000 --> 39:08.710
That's where I met
my Earth Angel

39:08.710 --> 39:11.790
and had the most amazing night
of my life.

39:13.460 --> 39:15.920
So this mystery woman --
did she speak authoritatively

39:15.920 --> 39:18.880
like she knew all the answers
and you were, like, an idiot?

39:18.880 --> 39:21.460
Nah. This was love.

39:21.460 --> 39:25.330
I can tell because it hurts
so much to be without her.

39:25.330 --> 39:28.080
But I kind of love
how much it hurts.

39:28.080 --> 39:30.000
Makes me feel alive.

39:30.000 --> 39:32.290
Like, there's meaning
to life, you know?

39:32.290 --> 39:34.790
Yeah.

39:34.790 --> 39:36.710
Yes, I do.

39:36.710 --> 39:38.120
That's why I want
to document this.

39:38.120 --> 39:40.250
Show our grandchildren.

39:42.040 --> 39:45.120
What makes you think
you'll ever see her again?

39:45.120 --> 39:48.330
Hm. The universe sent me
an angel, Kev.

39:48.330 --> 39:51.000
The universe
doesn't make mistakes.

39:51.000 --> 39:53.330
I'll see her again.

39:53.330 --> 40:01.620
♪♪

40:01.620 --> 40:09.670
♪♪

40:09.670 --> 40:18.170
♪♪

40:18.170 --> 40:22.620
♪ A frosty Christmas Eve ♪

40:22.620 --> 40:27.330
♪ When the stars were shining ♪

40:27.330 --> 40:32.250
♪ I traveled for the home ♪

40:32.250 --> 40:36.880
♪ Where westward
falls the hill ♪

40:36.880 --> 40:41.580
♪ And for many, many a village ♪

40:41.580 --> 40:42.710
♪ In the darkness... ♪

40:42.710 --> 40:44.420
More pretzels?

40:44.420 --> 40:48.250
Just because something is free
doesn't mean stuff your face.

40:48.250 --> 40:50.380
Did you really
slow-dance with Tyler

40:50.380 --> 40:51.960
to a mariachi band
in Laos?

40:51.960 --> 40:53.670
You have to tell me.

40:53.670 --> 40:58.080
Do I look like I have time for
casual meetups in East Asia?

40:58.080 --> 40:59.830
Does that even
sound like me?

41:01.210 --> 41:04.170
-No, I guess not.
-Okay.

41:04.170 --> 41:06.380
Wait. You didn't
answer the question.

41:06.380 --> 41:08.170
You need to forget
this foolishness

41:08.170 --> 41:11.330
and get your mind
back in the game.

41:11.330 --> 41:13.880
Fine. But only because

41:13.880 --> 41:16.420
I was already thinking
about Vong's baby anyway.

41:16.420 --> 41:18.500
♪ Heard music in the fields ♪

41:18.500 --> 41:20.420
Do you think
she'll be alright?

41:20.420 --> 41:23.540
She's so helpless.

41:23.540 --> 41:26.460
She'll be fine.

41:26.460 --> 41:28.620
Trust me.

41:28.620 --> 41:31.790
Pretty optimistic for somebody
who had lost all hope.

41:31.790 --> 41:34.420
Because...

41:34.420 --> 41:38.540
I now know something
I didn't know before.

41:38.540 --> 41:40.880
What you do matters.

41:40.880 --> 41:44.290
The -- The smallest
act of kindness,

41:44.290 --> 41:48.710
the -- the simplest
expression of love...

41:48.710 --> 41:53.710
it -- it grows.

41:53.710 --> 41:56.620
It reverberates
through the world...

41:56.620 --> 41:58.000
[ Laya fusses ]

41:58.000 --> 42:01.380
...through the universe.

42:01.380 --> 42:05.040
And it's a light
that's more powerful

42:05.040 --> 42:07.580
than any force
of darkness.

42:07.580 --> 42:10.000
♪ By the riches of the times ♪

42:10.000 --> 42:12.080
I know now...
Open it.

42:12.080 --> 42:15.540
...more than I've
ever known before...

42:15.540 --> 42:17.620
[ Laughs ]

42:17.620 --> 42:19.500
[ Reese squeals ]
...that the world is good.

42:19.500 --> 42:21.040
Ooh, they're
delicious.

42:21.040 --> 42:22.750
Did you seriously
just eat that?

42:22.750 --> 42:24.670
They're so good.
A little crunchy.
No!

42:26.580 --> 42:33.960
♪♪

42:33.960 --> 42:41.330
♪♪

42:41.330 --> 42:48.540
♪♪

42:48.540 --> 42:55.880
♪♪
